<br>
1) Caster/pet owner drops below 20% or 40% health. Pet now automatically jumps in and starts to shield you from the blows for 12 seconds. (that's the duration for /shield)<br>
<br>
2) Pets defend their master through this method (provided you have a warrior pet) and give you a little time to heal/nuke/flee/gate/whatever you can do in 12 seconds, if your pet doesn't get slaughtered.<br>
<br>
Think about at what times a pet owner would be taking damage like that. Beastlords? Pretty regularly, so they'd get more use out of it in normal xps situations. Magicians? When we're taking additional fire from adds/rampage or tanking for our pet (pet's gotta be over like 35, I think).<br>
<br>
In normal situations, it's a moot point. Magicians don't take hits. When you're in situations where you're dropping below 40% health from melee damage, you probably need the 12 seconds of cover. Makes PvP a little more interesting as you can't just ignore the pet as easily (pet absorbs blows for a li'l while)<br>
<br>
On them actually being used to shield others, Pets have no affinity for anyone else but their master. Why would they defend anyone else but you? Also, Verant isn't likely to give us a /pet shield &lt;target&gt; command, but rather /pet shield on and /pet shield off toggles to turn the behavior on and off, sorta like taunt. (ie: you can't say /pet taunt &lt;target&gt;).<br>
<br>
I think this is a good thing, myself. Give me 12 seconds to Gate if I must while my pet covers my escape? Most cool <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uslagnath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slagnath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/02 3:53:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=768.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.warcraft.org/resources/war3ss/full/w3cs10.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pft. Shield Nerf.</span><hr size=1> at first i was like neato! yay for mages! yay for necro/pet casters.<br>
